# hub/userlist — exam accounts for the JupyterHub front-end (variant "hub").
#
# One account per line:    username:password:lab[:admin]
#
#   lab    full    → polyglot lab image (Python, R, Julia, C, C++, Java, …)
#          python  → Python-only lab image
#          both    → student picks one of the two at login
#   admin  → JupyterHub admin panel (see/stop all user servers)
#
# No self-registration: only accounts in this file can log in. Edits apply on
# the next login — no hub restart needed. Keep usernames to letters, digits,
# - and _ (they become container names and results/ folder names).
#
# ./run.sh start hub  copies this example to hub/userlist if it is missing.
# hub/userlist is gitignored — real passwords never land in git.
alice:wonderland:full
bob:builder:python
carol:christmas:both
teacher:changeme:both:admin
